    <name>
				<text>10.1.2.14 Dividing complex numbers</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise </p>
<p>If <span class="math inline">\(z={@exp1@}\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(w={@exp2@}\)</span> find <span class="math inline">\(\displaystyle \frac{2z+3w}{2z-3w}\)</span>.</p>
<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:Result]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We first find \(\displaystyle \frac{2z+3w}{2z-3w}\) by substituting \(z ={@exp1@}\) and \(w={@exp2@}\) and simplifing.</p>
<p>\[ \frac{2z+3w}{2z-3w} = \frac{2({@exp1@})+3({@exp2@})}{2({@exp1@})-3({@exp2@})} = \frac{{@num1@}}{{@den1@}}.\];</p>
<p>Multiplying the top and bottom by the conjugate of the denominator gives</p>
<p>\[ \frac{{@num1@}}{{@den1@}} \times \frac{{@conjugate(den1)@}}{{@conjugate(den1)@}} = 
 \frac{{@ratsimp(num1*conjugate(den1))@}}{{@ratsimp(den1*conjugate(den1))@}} ={@correctanswer@}.\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1.0000000</defaultgrade>
    <penalty>0.1000000</penalty>
    <hidden>0</hidden>
    <idnumber></idnumber>
    <stackversion>
				<text>2022071300</text>
		</stackversion>
    <questionvariables>
				<text>n1:ev(rand(5)+1,simp);
n2:ev(rand(5)+2,simp);
n3:ev(n1+rand(3)+1,simp);
n4:ev(n2+rand(2)+2,simp);
exp1: n1+n2*%i;
exp2: n3+n4*%i;
num:ev(2*exp1+3*exp2,simp);
num1:ratsimp(num);
den:ev(2*exp1-3*exp2,simp);
den1:ratsimp(den);

pval:ev((4*n1^2-9*n3^2+4*n2^2-9*n4^2)/(4*n1^2+9*n3^2-12*n1*n3+4*n2^2+9*n4^2-12*n2*n4),simp);

s:(2*n2+3*n4)*(2*n1-3*n3)-(2*n1+3*n3)*(2*n2-3*n4);
qval:ev(s/(4*n1^2+9*n3^2-12*n1*n3+4*n2^2+9*n4^2-12*n2*n4),simp);

correctanswer:ev(pval+qval*%i,simp);
correctanswer2:ev(pval,simp)+ev(qval,simp)*%i;
pvalwr:(n1*n3+n2*n4);
qvalwr:(n2*n3-n1*n4);
wrong1:ev(pvalwr+qvalwr*%i,simp)/(n3*n3+n4*n4);
simp:true
tempc:ev(n1*n3+n2*n3*%i - n1*n4*%i - n2*n4*(-1),simp)</text>
		</questionvariables>
